<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/30211145-val"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1612718346i/30211145._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/30211145-val">Val</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s the character’s writing. Octavia E. Butler&apos;s works are wonderful, unique, and certainly transcending. Her other works are written well. I’ve read<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's the character’s writing. Octavia E. Butler's works are wonderful, unique, and certainly transcending. Her other works are written well. I’ve read most all of her books. I studied her in college. This woman’s stories should be required reading in schools. Learn about the author. Watch some of her interviews. This woman has contributed to the human race tremendously, and helped me to look through a different lens. Exactly what a story should do -- take me somewhere else, and suspend my disbelief. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
