<div id="review_1522180077" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1522180077" />
    <a title="Dannii Elle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44487975-dannii-elle"><img alt="Dannii Elle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623521403p2/44487975.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1522180077?book_show_action=true">Oct 03, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dannii Elle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dannii Elle" href="/user/show/44487975-dannii-elle">Dannii Elle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44487975-dannii-elle?shelf=science-fiction-sagacity">science-fiction-sagacity</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/44487975-dannii-elle?shelf=adult-books-read">adult-books-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1522180077" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5429566200291070993">This is a really intense and interesting insight into a scarily believable future of our world. With water scarce and sold at an all-time premium and with the subsequent abolishment of the structured societal hierarchy as we know it, anarchy reigns on Earth.<br/><br/>Lauren lives a relatively safe life inside the confines of her walled community, on the outskirts of LA. Lauren&apos;s preacher father strove to create a community that thrived on the now almost-obsolete religious teachings he believes in. He exce</span>
  <span id="freeText5429566200291070993" style="display:none">This is a really intense and interesting insight into a scarily believable future of our world. With water scarce and sold at an all-time premium and with the subsequent abolishment of the structured societal hierarchy as we know it, anarchy reigns on Earth.<br /><br />Lauren lives a relatively safe life inside the confines of her walled community, on the outskirts of LA. Lauren's preacher father strove to create a community that thrived on the now almost-obsolete religious teachings he believes in. He excelled in his endeavour... until he didn't. Lauren then finds herself thrust into a new world she knows little about and must find her own way of viewing all it contains, without her father's guidance.<br /><br />I really liked how this managed to be religious without being overly preachy and the creation of Lauren's Earthseed beliefs was fascinating. This was both an insight to religion, from both a believer and a non-believer's perspective, as well as a look at how this way of thinking adapts to a dystopian world where little faith remains. Lauren is very much an active agent of change and her new way of thinking could just be humanity's salvation.<br /><br />Whilst these concepts put forward some interesting points of discussion, I did find the plot initially a little slow building. This was a fascinating insight to a recognisable yet ravaged world but the content of the plot did not progress much from this point, for quite some time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5429566200291070993" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


